posts.title: Eternal Recurrence
posts.description:
So Nietzsche's idea of Eternal Recurrence kind of got stuck in my head: the concept that we are doomed to live the same life over and over again forever, as matter can only be arranged in a finite number of ways.
I ended up drawing this in a bar after mulling the concept over for a while. A bit dark, I know -- but it did serve to generally get me left alone. Am I the only person who goes to bars to be alone?

posts.title: Dulce Bellum Inexpertis
posts.description:
A few years back I used to design and produce embroidered patches. I was part of several patch collector groups, and making limited runs of original designs was a pretty decent way of making spare money.
Unfortunately, the communities were decidedly right-wing and became quite toxic over time. Would that there were communities that weren't completely nuts, I never would have given up my side hustle.
Some good did come out of it, though. I produced an entire series of scribbled originals that served as card inserts for the patches themselves. This one, in particular, comes with the Latin phrase "Dulce bellum inexpertis" which means, "war is sweet to those who haven't experienced it."

Anyhow, it's pretty nonconformist so...

madness.title: Trapped
madness.description:
It fits the bill mostly. I'm not sure that the end result could be considered charming, but it's definitely disturbing.
Ever felt like you were trapped inside your own head, and simply going through the motions? Yeah. This was the first thing I produced after taking a five-year break from art entirely. Guess it's like riding a bike.

madness.title: Dryad
madness.prompt: A fifty foot statue of tasteful nudity
madness.description:
Though it's not quite a statue, I think it fits the bill of tasteful. I rarely do nudes. I don't see the point.
This, however, was originally produced for a small breast cancer charity fundraiser. She is done entirely in stippling (tiny dots), and took me a little over two weeks to produce working ten hours a day, weekends included.
